### Team Task Manager — REST smoke tests (REST Client / VS Code extension)
### 1. Create variables after login
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api
@token = <paste_jwt_here>

### Health (root, not under /api)
GET http://localhost:5000/health

### Sign up (adjust email to stay unique)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Demo Member",
  "email": "demo.member+sandbox@company.com",
  "password": "Str0ng#Pass!"
}

### Login seed admin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@company.com",
  "password": "Admin123!"
}

### Me
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Admin-only directory
GET {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Projects collection
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Create project (admin)
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Innovation backlog",
  "description": "Track discovery spikes",
  "status": "Not Started",
  "startDate": "2026-05-01",
  "endDate": "2026-12-31"
}

### Tasks with filters + overdue shortcut
GET {{baseUrl}}/tasks?overdue=true
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Member status patch (must be assignee)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/tasks/TASK_OBJECT_ID/status
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "Review"
}

### Dashboard aggregate
GET {{baseUrl}}/dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
